definition.value: Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells with small endothelial spaces, occurring in the face.
A condition in which superficial veins (i.e., veins just under the skin) are more conspicuous or noticeable than normal.

label.value: Skin dimple over apex of long bone angulation

definition.value: A skin texture that is unusually soft (and may feel silky), and has a malleable consistency resembling that of dough.
